<TEXT>
there has been a sharp rise in antisemitic 
incidents that stem from opposition to israel the antidefamation 
league of bnai brith reported tuesday 
so far this year 88 out of 443 antisemitic incidents reported 
in the united states have had an element of antiisraeli sentiment 
according to a report by the adl which monitors outbreaks of 
racism and antisemitism 
by contrast there were only three such incidents out of 1018 
antisemitic episodes reported for all of last year 
this years antiisraeli incidents appeared to be prompted by 
palestinian unrest in the occupied territories the west bank and 
gaza strip the adl report said 
abraham foxman the groups national director said the 
incidents represented the first time since the founding of the 
state of israel 40 years ago that there has been a significant 
outbreak of middle eastrelated antisemitic incidents in this 
country 
the incidents included vandalism and arson attacks on 
synagogues telephone threats to jewish organizations and other 
forms of verbal harassment 
california led all states in reports of politically motivated 
antisemitism with 12 vandalism cases and 13 harassment incidents 
followed by illinois florida minnesota massachusetts and 
pennsylvania the adl said 
the figures are based on reports gathered by the adls 31 
regional offices 
