<TEXT>
two climbers trapped 
overnight by a storm completed their ascent up half dome with the 
help of rescuers and then hiked 8 miles to the yosemite valley 
floor a park spokeswoman said 
charley hampson 33 and bill enger 32 both of seattle were 
4200 feet above the valley when they called for help about 10 am 
sunday spokeswoman mallory smith said monday 
the men who began a twoday climb of the rocks northwest face 
on saturday shouted to climbers above them to get help because the 
storm which dumped rain and snow on them and froze their ropes 
overnight 
a national park service helicopter lowered fresh ropes sleeping 
bags warm clothes and food by about 5 pm sunday smith said it 
then lowered two rescue climbers who helped the two climb the 
remaining 600 feet to safety 
