<TEXT>
when lt gov l douglas wilder was growing 
up in this former confederate capital he waited on tables at 
political dinners in the citys segregated clubs and hotels 
next year wilder could land a job in virginias executive 
mansion as the host of such dinners and the nations first 
elected black governor 
the 57yearold wilder whose grandparents were slaves already 
is the highestranking black elected state official in the country 
although he has not yet announced his candidacy he would be the 
favorite to win the democratic nomination for governor next summer 
mark rozell a political scientist at mary washington college in 
fredericksburg said wilder has no strong opposition within the 
party and among potential republican opponents next november only 
sen paul s trible jr seems at this point to pose a major threat 
to wilders election 
trible is not seeking reelection to the senate this year and 
has not said whether he will run for governor in 1989 
wilder the youngest of eight children grew up in richmond he 
studied chemistry at virginia union university then enlisted in 
the army and won a bronze star for bravery in korea 
he went to law school at howard university and opened a law 
practice here in 1959 ten years later he ran for a virginia 
senate vacancy when other local black leaders showed no interest 
he became the first black to sit in the chamber since 
reconstruction 
in the senate wilder was recognized as a skilled debater who 
quickly learned the rules of parliamentary procedure although his 
early image was that of a firebrand he was never considered a 
militant 
wilder was instrumental in the states adoption of a holiday 
honoring slain civil rights leader martin luther king jr he also 
lobbied unsuccessfully to change lyrics that blacks found offensive 
in the state song carry me back to old virginia 
wilder combined the role of maverick with that of an insider in 
1982 he singlehandedly scuttled the us senate ambition of 
fellow democrat owen b pickett because pickett dared to invoke the 
name of virginias conservative leader harry f byrd jr a us 
senator who left the democratic party in 1970 to become an 
independent the byrd organization had dominated the state for 50 
years 
two years later in july 1984 wilder announced for the 
democratic nomination for lieutenant governor no serious 
opposition arose within the party during the next year and he was 
nominated in june 1985 when virginia democrats also nominated a 
woman for attorney general there were predictions that the party 
was headed for disaster 
but wilder played down his race and offered the image of a 
moderate native son in the tradition of thendemocratic gov 
charles s robb 
a combination of robbs popularity mistakes by wilders gop 
opponent and a tour of the state by wilder helped turn the 
predicted disaster into the second straight democratic sweep of the 
states top three offices 
wilders performance in the administration of gov gerald l 
baliles who cannot by law succeed himself has been mostly lowkey 
however wilder engaged in a wellpublicized feud with robb 
during his first year in office over how much credit robb deserved 
for the 1985 victory wilder also has criticized the 
administrations tax increases for road construction and made a 
show this year of pushing over baliles objections for a repeal 
of the sales tax on overthecounter drugs 
the lieutenant governors major prospective competitor for the 
gubernatorial nomination stepped aside in march when attorney 
general mary sue terry announced that she would seek another term 
in office 
baliles acknowledged this month in a college commencement 
address that wilder could make history next year by becoming the 
first black to lead the states democratic ticket 
baliles office said no endorsement was intended but observers 
said the comment amounted to a warning to potential rivals to stay 
out of wilders way 
wilder is expected to announce his political plans this summer 
according to rozell wilders race may not prevent him from 
becoming governor of the old dominion because of changes over the 
past 20 years in the states population and its attitudes about 20 
percent of virginians are black and the state also has a large 
progressiveminded population in the northern corridor adjoining 
the nations capital 
no black has ever been elected governor in this country in 1986 
los angeles democratic mayor thomas bradley and william lucas a 
republican county executive in michigan both were nominated by 
their parties but lost the election bradley also had failed in his 
first race for governor in 1982 
the only black to serve as a us governor was pinckney bs 
pinchback the lieutenant governor of louisiana who became acting 
governor for six weeks in 18721873 after the governor was 
impeached 
</TEXT>
