of the pacifying russian countryside it is in the churches they 
lift their belltowers graceful shapely all different high over 
mundane timber and thatch from villages that are cutoff and 
invisible to each other they soar to the same heaven people were 
always selfish and often unkind but the evening chimes used to 
ring out floating over the villages fields and woods reminding 
them that they must abandon trivial concerns of this world and give 
time and thought to eternity 
in our prayers we may keep that image in mind the thought that 
the bells may ring again sounding throughout moscow and across the 
countryside clamoring for joy in their newfound freedom well ive 
talked long enough im sure you have many questions and many 
things on your mind and im anxious to hear what you have to say 
