where the reagans are staying during the summit 
the reagans really seem to appreciate american music in 
general nancy seems to know all the standards you can see her 
mouthing the words the grayhaired 67yearold brubeck said in 
an interview monday 
as for the president a former hollywood actor brubeck recalled 
that at a feb 21 performance at the white house for governors 
he told me how much he loved the big bands and how much they were 
a part of american history 
brubeck is no stranger to the halls of power he was the first 
jazz musician to play at the white house and has entertained every 
president since john f kennedy 
he met the gorbachevs but didnt have a chance to talk to them 
or play for them at the previous summit state dinner at the white 
house last december that dinner produced one of the most memorable 
moments of the washington summit the gorbachevs singing along as 
the american classical pianist van cliburn played the russian 
standard moscow nights 
asked if he would follow in van cliburns footsteps with the 
dixieland jazz version of the song renamed midnight in moscow 
brubeck said were prepared to play it if someone asks but its 
been done so many times 
but in typical brubeckian manner if its played itll be with 
a twist in fivefour rhythm it can be done he assured a 
doubting reporter 
in honor of the occasion brubeck has dug up the real 
ambassadors a song he wrote in 1958 for a musical that featured 
trumpeter louis armstrong running the world for a day 
although the gorbachevs wont hear it because brubeck plans to 
play only an instrumental version of the song one line speaks of 
armstrong using music to bring peace the next time around its 
a session where we jam the blues khrushchev pounding both his 
shoes couldnt have the final say if i was king for a day 
khrushchev who pounded a shoe on a desk at the united nations 
in 1960 was no jazz lover when i hear jazz its as if i had 
gas on the stomach he said in december 1963 
at the other extreme yuri andropov the former kgb chief who 
led the soviet union from november 1982 until his death in february 
1984 was reputed to be a jazz fan 
but although mrs gorbachev has showed up at several classical 
music concerts little is known about the kremlin couples musical 
tastes 
i keep asking everyone if gorbachev likes jazz but no one 
seems to know says brubecks 36yearold son chris who plays 
bass guitar and trombone in the group they all say andropov 
liked jazz and had a huge record collection 
the elder brubeck who says hes played in most countries of the 
world from the dance halls to all the joints during his 
50year career believes jazz is a unique medium for espousing the 
american ideal of freedom 
to play jazz you have to have tremendous discipline and you 
are expected to use it in a free way theres no art form that 
represents america better than jazz he said 
and to many jazz lovers there is no single jazz standard better 
known than take five brubecks 1958 tune that was the first 
jazz single to go gold 
the wilton conn resident gave soviets who had heard him only 
