<TEXT>
the nations environmental statistics are a 
disgrace with billiondollar decisions turning on the readings of 
a handful of monitoring instruments says a veteran washington 
environmental analyst calling for a bureau of environmental 
statistics 
such a bureau could direct attention and spending to needed 
areas avoid costly unnecessary programs and keep bureaucrats 
