<TEXT>
a small fishing boat with three people 
aboard hit a mine and exploded in the gulf of oman on tuesday 
killing one fisherman and injuring two united arab emirates 
officials said 
the official emirates news agency quoted an interior ministry 
statement as saying the incident occurred off dednah 20 miles 
south of the entrance to the strait of hormuz 
the waters are just north of a major anchorage off khor fakkan 
that is used by tankers and other commercial vessels going to and 
from the persian gulf the anchorage is the staging area for us 
navyescorted convoys of americanflagged kuwaiti tankers bound for 
kuwait 
there was no word on whether the mine was floating free or 
tethered to the floor of the gulf 
the area was plagued by a spate of mines last fall and at least 
two vessels were hit one a small offshore supply boat sank and 
six crewmen died 
the incidents which the united states and other officials 
blamed on iran prompted uae authorities to close the anchorage 
temporarily and were a factor in britain and france deciding to 
dispatch mine sweepers to the gulf region 
some of those craft eventually cleared the area and no mines 
had been reported in the gulf of oman for several months prior to 
tuesdays incident 
the ministry said all of the victims tuesday were indians the 
two survivors were rescued by another fishing boat and taken for 
treatment to fujairah another port down the coast it said 
salvage workers at fujairah were attempting to seal off leaking 
ammonia from a liberianflag norwegianowned gas tanker towed 
there after being severely damaged in an iranian gunboat attack on 
thursday 
lloyds shipping intelligence unit in london said salvage 
officials may unload the ammonia cargo lloyds officials said the 
cargo had formed a poisonous cloud around one of the dutch 
salvage tugboats that assisted the damaged vessel 
lloyds said the ship the 15530ton mundogas rio suffered 
more minor damage on monday in a blast believed caused by a 
rocketpropelled grenade that had earlier failed to explode 
