issues also 55 percent of southerners said the campaigns provide 
a good discussion belying criticism of the super tuesday regional 
primary as a superficial media event 
a plurality of all respondents and a majority of southerners 
said super tuesday was a good idea and 54 percent of the 
respondents said regional primaries should be held in the future 
while 41 percent of those polled said they have been following 
this years primary campaigns regularly 50 percent said they paid 
occasional attention and 9 percent said they followed the primaries 
hardly at all or not at all 
the media generalassociated press poll consisted of telephone 
interviews april 29may 8 with a randomly selected sample of 1204 
adults across the nation the margin of error was plus or minus 
three percentage points 
