speaking on the first day of a special fourweek un session on 
disarmament hansen added that the united states will not try to 
pass a un resolution calling for arms cuts by third world nations 
hansen assistant director of the us arms control and 
disarmament agency said we are not going to come here and 
insist that developing countries somehow change their defense 
priorities for the acquisition of arms 
of course we would like them to spend less money on arms and 
