arms control with progress on human rights issues 
the un general assembly stated in 1979 that the united nations 
should play a central role in disarmament and that complete 
nuclear disarmament was the priority 
no breakthroughs are expected to emerge at this un session 
during which at least 25 presidents and prime ministers are 
scheduled to address the general assembly 
