times 
but since most women reported never offering such resistance 
the result does not mean that men can safely ignore womens 
refusals when a woman says no chances are that she means it 
and regardless of the incidence of token resistance if the woman 
means no and the man persists it is rape wrote texas aampm 
university researchers charlene muehlenhard and lisa hollabaugh 
they gave an anonymous questionnaire to 610 female students 
average age 19 at their school results appear in the may issue of 
the journal of personality and social psychology 
twentythree percent of the 240 coeds who offred token 
resistance said manipulative reasons such as gameplaying anger 
with the man or desire to be in control were at least moderately 
important reasons for resisting about an equal percentage cited 
such reasons as fear of appearing promiscuous fear of catching 
disease or uncertainty about their partners feelings 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
suramin a drug long used to treat parasite 
infections is being tested for the first time as a way to attack 
cancer 
doctors from the american cancer society used it on 10 people 
with advanced spreading cases of cancer of the adrenal gland 
although it did not cure their disease suramin seemed to slow the 
cancer by blocking body chemicals known as growth factors 
tumors need these substances to promote their own growth 
we believe that suramin is the first of a class of growth 
factorinhibiting drugs said dr cy a stein even if it is 
not the ideal drug it is helping us to learn what scheme is 
necessary to stop tumors from growing by inhibiting their growth 
factors 
in two of the patients tumors were reduced by more than 50 
percent while those in two others decreased by 25 to 50 percent 
the disease remained stable in three while progressing in three 
stein said that once the drug was stopped the cancer recurred 
rapidly doctors are now considering trying suramin on other forms 
of cancer and combining it with standard chemotherapy drugs 
the most serious side effect was nerve damage which doctors 
said may limit how long people can stay on suramin 
the results were reported at a recent meeting of the american 
society of clinical oncology 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
tiny beads coated with cancerkilling drugs 
are being tested to slow progression of liver cancer a uniformly 
fatal disease 
the treatment called chemoembolization uses beads of starch 
that have been treated with chemotherapy medicines to temporarily 
dam up the hepatic artery the major artery that supplies the liver 
this deprives the tumor of blood while putting it in contact 
with drugs doctors say the combination can stop the growth of the 
tumor and sometimes shrink it 
in a few days the starch is absorbed into the body and blood 
flow resumes during the temporary blockade the liver continues to 
receive blood through the portal vein 
among 30 patients who received the experimental treatment at the 
university of california san francisco two had dramatic 
responses one had no recurrence of the tumor for 16 months and the 
other for over two years in about threequarters the tumor shrank 
significantly or temporarily stopped growing 
dr alan venook who outlined the results at a recent american 
society of clinical oncology meeting said the new treatment 
provides temporary relief from the spread of the disease but is not 
a cure 
it is better than anything else around he said some 
patients have shown remarkable improvement but the therapy needs 
further development 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

